jdk 1.8 has added java.time package

Java 8 introduced new Api for Date and Time to overcome shortcomings of Older jav.util.Data and Time Api
Date and Calendar were not thread safe in Java 7 where as in Java 8 are immutable and thread safe

Api design and understanding is easy
Timezone handling is easy in java 8

LocalDate : The LocalDate represents a date in ISO format (yyyy-MM-dd) without time.
It can be used for pay day . Birthday etc.

Compatibilty With Date and Calendar before Java 8 to Java 8 time API:

Java 8 has added toInstant method to convert Date and Calendar APi to
new Java8 Date and Time Api